eir own different perspectives.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aDiscourse analysiszGermany. 0aGuilt and culturezGermany. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)xCauses. 0aNational socialismxMoral and ethical aspects. 4aDeutsch /Sprache. 4aDiskurs. 4aNachkriegszeit (Weltkrieg II). 4aSchuld. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh1 aKämper, Heidrun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2005z9783110277111oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2005z9783110276886oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311018855440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311090733940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110907339423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110907339/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2005  aZDB-23-DGGb2005  aZDB-23-GHIc2000d2014